  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of integrated food security through restocking and cash for work and nutrition through awareness to most vulnerable drought and sagoar cyclone effected population in Badhan and Taleh Districts.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to enhance immediate food access by increasing the purchasing power of the beneficiaries through conditional cash grants as well as restocking of the lost livelihoods (goats) to the pastoral livelihood to these largely pastoralist communities that already lost up to 70 per cent of their livestock due to four consecutive seasons of below normal rains, as well as due to the impact of the cyclone Sagar, are at risk of slipping to crisis (IPC 3).The project targets the most vulnerable households who were affected by the prevailing drought. The drought situation has severely and directly affected pastoral and agro-pastoral communities of the target locations whose sources of food, income and water are diminishing and increasingly at risk. The situation led to household food insecurity, reduction/lack of safe water. The project entails  provision of cash plus grant for  180 households for three (3) months with full MEB ( 100 HHs in Badhan and 80 in Talex ), Restocking of 104 HH for the families that lost their livestock and willing to resume their nomad life with 10 heads of goats (9 lactating and one male)  and providing supplements blocks 10 KG per HH, vaccinate against PPR/SGP and deworm to restocking targeted beneficiaries.  284 HHs are expected to benefit the project in Total.</narrative>
  </description>
